---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Perfumery — Fragrance Terms That Score"
  description="Perfumery and fragrance words valid in Scrabble with scoring. MYRRH 13pts, MUSK 10pts, SCENT 7pts. Aromatic vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble perfumery words, fragrance scrabble terms, myrrh scrabble points, musk scrabble, scent scrabble word, perfume words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Perfumery — Fragrance Terms That Score","description":"Perfumery and fragrance words valid in Scrabble with scoring. MYRRH 13pts, MUSK 10pts, SCENT 7pts.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-perfumery"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is MYRRH in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"MYRRH scores 13 points (M=3, Y=4, R=1, R=1, H=4). It uses Y (4pts) and H (4pts) effectively plus M (3pts). Compact and efficient at 2.6 points per tile."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is MUSK a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! MUSK scores 10 points (M=3, U=1, S=1, K=5) and is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS. The K tile provides half the word's value. Refers to a strong-smelling perfume base."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What perfumery words work in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Top perfumery words include MYRRH (13pts), MUSKY (14pts), MUSK (10pts), SPICY (12pts), BALM (8pts), SCENT (7pts), and AROMA (7pts). Fragrance vocabulary uses M, Y, K, and H tiles that score well for their length."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Perfumery — Fragrance Terms That Score</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Perfumery brings ancient and exotic words into Scrabble — MYRRH from biblical incense, MUSK from the animal kingdom, ATTAR from Persian rose oil. These terms are short (4-5 letters) with high-value consonants like K, H, and Y, making them efficient scorers for tight boards.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MUSKY</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MYRRH</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SPICY</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MUSK</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top Perfumery Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">MUSKY — 14 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">M=3, U=1, S=1, K=5, Y=4 · 5 letters · K + Y powerhouse</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">MUSKY delivers 14 points from 5 tiles (2.8 per tile). The K tile (5pts) and Y (4pts) drive most of the score, while M (3pts) adds a comfortable buffer. A fragrance adjective that hits hard in compact positions.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🕯️ MYRRH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · M=3, Y=4, R=1, R=1, H=4 · Double R + H</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌶️ SPICY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · S=1, P=3, I=1, C=3, Y=4 · P + C + Y</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🦌 MUSK</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · M=3, U=1, S=1, K=5 · K tile value</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧴 BALM</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · B=3, A=1, L=1, M=3 · Two 3-pointers</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Fragrance Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AROMA</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SCENT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WOODY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">RESIN</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ATTAR</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FLORAL</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Perfumery Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">MYRRH is an H-tile champion:</span> H (4pts) pairs poorly with most consonants. MYRRH puts H at the end after double R — no vowels needed beyond Y acting as one. Unique letter pattern opponents won't see coming.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">MUSKY upgrades MUSK:</span> If MUSK is on the board or you have Y too, MUSKY scores 14 points. The Y addition is always worth it — 4 extra points for one tile is a great trade.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Perfume words fit tight boards:</span> MUSK (4 letters), MYRRH (5), BALM (4), SCENT (5) — all compact. In endgame positions where the board is locked, these short words reach spots bingos can't.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Perfumery words are <span class="text-white font-medium">endgame specialists</span>. Short (4-5 letters), dense scoring (10-14pts), and heavy on consonants hard to play elsewhere. MYRRH, MUSK, and MUSKY belong in every player's endgame toolkit.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-cooking/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Cooking</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-nature-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Nature Words</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-with-k/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words with K</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid fragrance word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
